 Former Tottenham Hotspur midfielder Christian Eriksen has offered himself to Real Madrid and Atletico Madrid, according to report. Eriksen joined Inter Milan from Premier League side last winter but manager Antonio Conte feels he is not compatible with his style of football. Vazquez & Asensio on target as Real Madrid beat Celta Vigo to move top of La Liga The Serie A team has now offered him to Real Madrid and Atletico Madrid, last season he was one of the most sought-after players when he left for Serie A. Real Madrid has other targets other than Eriksen with Bayern Munich defender David Alaba on the radar of the Santiago Bernabeu outfit and in the summer they are keen on signing Erling Haaland and Kylian Mbappe. The Dane was seen as a bargain when he moved to Inter for 20 million euros last winter, but reported spats with Conte have frozen him out of the picture.